<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">
This species has been adequately described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy" box="[736,890,366,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1973) The fruit flies (Tephritidae-Diptera) of Thailand and bordering countries. Pacific Insects Monograph, 31, 1 - 353." type="journal article" year="1973">
Hardy (
<number box="[823,881,367,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" value="1973.0">1973</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock" box="[947,1253,366,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" refString="Hancock, D. L. &amp; Drew, R. A. I. (1999) Bamboo-shoot fruit flies of Asia (Diptera: Tephritidae: Ceratitidinae). Journal of Natural History, 33, 633 - 775. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 002229399300164" type="journal article" year="1999">
Hancock and Drew (
<number box="[1184,1245,367,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Hardy" authorityName="Hardy" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Acroceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">A. tomentosa</emphasis>
Hardy
</taxonomicName>
in possessing costal band interrupted by a hyaline transverse band just beyond cell sc, but differs in having scutellum entirely black except for a yellow mark on each side at base of basal scutellar setae and dark fuscous femora. It is now known from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[690,750,474,499]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[761,874,474,499]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[885,987,474,499]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1052,475,498]" name="Laos" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Laos</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1107,1220,474,499]" name="Indonesia" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
